	<Text>The Purple Heart was originally established by George Washington in 1782. The medal was reestablished in 1932 by the War Department for Army personnel and in 1943 by the Navy Department for the Navy and Marine Corps. It is awarded to military personnel who are wounded in action while serving with the armed forces of the United States. It is also awarded posthumously to the next of kin of persons killed or having died from wounds received in action after April 5, 1917.
</Text>
